Subject: HSBC 2018 Application - Invitation to Online Immersive Assessment
Text:
Dear Andre,

We are pleased to confirm that further to your application to the Graduate - Global Banking & Markets - Global Banking - Investment Banking - North America - USA - New York, you have successfully met our initial screening criteria.  We would now like to invite you to the next stage of the assessment process.

Assessment details:
The next stage of the assessment consists of an online immersive assessment.
The information gathered from these tests forms one part of the selection procedure and provides useful additional information that we cannot gain from the other parts of the process.
This is a video delivered documentary assessment covering behaviours, values, and HSBC specific numerical reasoning and critical analyst items.  Therefore we recommend that you have a calculator, pen and paper to hand before you start the assessment.
For the best experience you should access the assessments using a common operating system and browser.
Should you experience any technical difficulties, please contact our Support Technical Team on hsbcsupport@gtios.com

Completing the assessments:
To access your application please click on the link below where you will be able to complete the online testing:    https://earlycareers.hsbc.gtios.com
We recommend that you identify a time to complete this assessment when you will not be disturbed by others, and feeling at your best.  We recommend you have audio available to you whilst completing, however should you wish to use subtitles then please click on the CC button in the bottom right-hand corner as the video plays.

Once you have accessed your application, links to your assessment will be displayed.
Answer the questions steadily with no distractions or input from any other person.  Please note that this assessment is not timed, but it is likely to take approximately 60 minutes to complete.

Deadline:
Candidates are allowed 7 days to complete the online assessment.

Next Steps:
If you meet the required benchmark for your online immersive assessment then you will go through to the Job Simulation assessment.

As a "Disability Confident" employer we actively encourage applications from a diverse talent pool.  Should you need any adjustments to be made for you in order to allow you to be properly considered for the role, please flag at the earliest opportunity and contact us at hsbc@graduatequeries.co.uk so that we can discuss with you further.

If in the meantime you do have any questions please do not hesitate to contact us.

Kind regards

HSBC Graduate Recruitment Team

Subject:
HSBC 2018 Application - Invitation to Online Job Simulation
 Assessment
Text:
Dear Andre,

We are pleased to confirm that you have successfully completed the online immersive assessment for the position of Graduate - Global Banking & Markets - Global Banking - Investment Banking - North America - USA - New York.
We would now like to invite you to the next stage of the assessment process.

Assessment details:
The next stage of the assessment consists of an online job simulation assessment.
The information gathered from these tests forms one part of the selection procedure and provides useful additional information that we cannot gain from the other parts of the process.
This is a video delivered business-line aligned assessment, covering verbal, written skills as well as behaviour and critical analysis. For the best experience you should access the assessments using a common operating system and browser.  We would also recommend, where possible, that you access the system using a computer/laptop with strong WiFi access to have the best experience.

Should you experience any technical difficulties, please contact our Support Technical Team on http://hirevue.force.com/E2Candidate

Completing the assessments:
To access your application please click on the link below where you will be able to complete the online assessment:    https://earlycareers.hsbc.gtios.com

Once you have accessed your application, links to your assessment will be displayed.
Answer the questions steadily with no distractions or input from any other person.  Please note that elements of this Job Simulation assessment are timed.

Deadline:
Candidates are allowed 7 days to complete the online assessment.

Next Steps:
If you meet the required benchmark for both online test your application will be reviewed in more detail with a view to progressing to the next stage of the selection process.

As a "Disability Confident" employer we actively encourage applications from a diverse talent pool. Should you need any adjustments to be made for you in order to allow you to be properly considered for the role, please flag at the earliest opportunity and contact us at hsbc@graduatequeries.co.uk so that we can discuss with you further.

If you have any questions please do not hesitate to contact us.

Kind regards
HSBC Graduate Recruitment Team

Subject: Thanks for applying to JMP Securities LLC
Text:
JMP Securities LLC

-------------------------------------------------------------------------=
------

Your application for the 2019 Investment Banking Analyst (NY/SF) job was =
submitted successfully.
Here's a copy of your application data for safekeeping:

-------------------------------------------------------------------------=
------

** PERSONAL INFORMATION **

Name: Andre Sealy

Email: andretsealy@gmail.com

Phone: 6462860995

Address: 1125 Park Place

** YOUR PROFILE **

Resume

Andre_Sealy_Resume.pdf

** APPLICATION DETAILS **

Cover Letter

Dear Kerry Porter (Recruiter)

I am a final year Finance and Economics student at Pace University and wo=
uld like to be considered for the Full-Time Investment Banking Analyst Pr=
ogram. Ashley Mistele (VP, DCM) has shared many exciting stories with me =
about the daily working life at JMP, and it sounds very attractive.

I=E2=80=99ve recently completed an overseas summer internship at a family=
-owned Venture Capital/Wealth Management firm called Lamivoie Capital Par=
tners, which was awarded to me through a scholarship that I won from the =
honors business society Beta Gamma Sigma. I had the opportunity to partic=
ipate in a start-up deal valued at $80M, produced a competitive landscape=
 report on the $40B technology industry in Shenzhen, China, and lead a te=
am of 3 interns to build a Discounted Cash Flow model for a $3B private e=
quity client. These experiences boosted my analytical and problem-solving=
 skills, while also allowing me to hone my leadership skills. My ability =
to get results in such a short time makes me confident that I can success=
fully continue my investment banking career as a first-year analyst.

To reiterate my interests in the program, I want to say that I=E2=80=99ve=
 always wanted to become a banker. I believe banking is a critical functi=
on of our society. Banking allows us to finance new businesses, allocate =
resources, and develop new products that improve our lives daily. I am im=
pressed by your track record of clients and transactions. JMP has helped =
a wide range of clients with their funding/advisory/capital restructure n=
eeds, especially firms with goods and services that I use on a daily basi=
s. I am also impressed by the significant amount of responsibility given =
to the analyst, and I look forward to joining and contributing to your fi=
rm.

With my economics and finance background, analytical skills, and results-=
driven focus, I feel that this program is a natural fit. I am excited abo=
ut the prospect of joining your team and your firm. Feel free to contact =
me any time using the information in my resume and within the application=
.

I look forward to the opportunity of discussing the program with you and =
hope to hear from you soon. =


Sincerely,

Andre Sealy

Answers

[YES] Have you completed coursework in finance and/or accounting?

If yes, please list relevant courses here:
Corporate Finance, Financial Accounting, Valuation, Quantitative Finance,=
 Private Equity

[YES] Have you completed an internship at an investment bank, private equ=
ity firm or venture capital firm?

List any finance-related extracurricular activities here:
Pace Investment Club, Wall Street Careers Workshop

Select your preferred location:
New York, NY

[YES] Are you on track to graduate with bachelor's degree in 2019?

[YES] Are you authorized to work lawfully in the United States for JMP Se=
curities LLC without requiring JMP Securities LLC to commence (=E2=80=9Cs=
ponsor=E2=80=9D) an immigration case in order to employ you (for example,=
 H-1B or other employment-based immigration case) either now or in the fu=
ture?

[YES] I hereby certify that the information I entereted is correct and tr=
ue





Didn=E2=80=99t apply? You can always withdraw your application or resume =
by following the link below:
